Conditions for the completeness of the spectral domain of a harmonizable process

by Roland Averkamp

Institut f√ºr Mathematische Stochastik, Albert-Ludwigs Universit√§t Freiburg, Eckerstrasse 1, 79104 Freiburg, Germany

Tel.: 49/761/203 5672; fax: 49/761/203 5661

Email: averkamp@pollux.mathematik.uni-freiburg.de


Received 11 September 1995; received in revised form 23 June 1997


Abstract 
We generalize a theorem of K√∂the and Toeplitz on unconditional bases in Hilbert spaces to Hilbert space-valued measures. This leads to a necessary and sufficient condition for the completeness of the spectral domain of a weakly harmonizable process whose shift operator exists and is invertible. A process in this class has a complete spectral domain if and only if it is the image of a stationary process under a topological isomorphism. (C) 1997 Elsevier Science B.V.
Keywords: Weakly harmonizable process; Bimeasure; Completeness of spectral domain; Shift operator
